<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Footer Variables Template</title>
    <style>
        body { font-family: Arial, sans-serif; margin: 2em; min-height: 100vh; display: flex; flex-direction: column; }
        main { flex: 1; }
        footer { background: #6c757d; color: white; padding: 1.5em; margin: 2em -2em -2em -2em; }
        .variable-section { background: #e9ecef; border: 1px solid #ced4da; padding: 1em; margin: 1em 0; border-radius: 5px; }
        .variable-list { font-family: monospace; background: #f8f9fa; padding: 1em; border-radius: 3px; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <main>
        <h1>Footer Variables Template</h1>

        <div class="variable-section">
            <h2>Footer Template Variables</h2>
            <p>This page demonstrates how footer templates can use variables for dynamic content:</p>

            <div class="variable-list">
                <strong>Available Variables:</strong><br>
                • {title} - Document title<br>
                • {date} - Current date<br>
                • {time} - Current time<br>
                • {pageNumber} - Current page number<br>
                • {totalPages} - Total page count<br>
                • {url} - Source URL<br>
                • {copyright} - Copyright information
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="variable-section">
            <h2>Testing Notes</h2>
            <p>Use this page to test:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Footer template variable substitution</li>
                <li>Dynamic content in PDF footers</li>
                <li>Page numbering and document metadata</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </main>

    <footer>
        <p><strong>Footer with Variables:</strong></p>
        <p>Page {pageNumber} of {totalPages} | Generated: <%= new Date().toLocaleDateString() %> at <%= new Date().toLocaleTimeString() %></p>
        <p>© 2024 Printeer Mock Server | Document: Footer Variables Demo</p>
    </footer>
</body>
</html>